  "texts": [
    "This corpus was annotated with four entities (rare disease, disease, symptom, and sign) by biomedical experts who had an inter-annotator agreement (IAA) F1-score of 83.5% under exact match, indicating a high level of annotation consistency and reliability.",
    "Specifically, the F1-score measures the IAA accounting for precision (proportion of correctly annotated entities) and recall (proportion of gold-standard entities that were annotated).",
    "Table 1 provides the entity definitions and summary statistics.",
    "Unlike corpora with distinct entity types, e.g., {person, location, organization} or {problem, test, treatment}, RareDis consists of entities with considerable semantic overlap.",
    "Specifically, rare diseases are a subset of diseases."
  ],
